2015-02-12  Alec Leamas  <leamas.alec@gmail.com>

	Build: daemons + tools ->  C++  (#79).
	This patch requires some brutal steps to build:
	make distclean; ./autogen.sh; ./autogen.sh; ./configure; make

	In the long term, it also breaks the checkpatch/checkfiles tool,
	which is C only. Not solved here.

2015-02-12  Alec Leamas  <leamas.alec@gmail.com>

	systemd/Makefile.am: Cleanup.

	doc: irrecord manpage update

	doc: tira_driver.html build  bugfix.

	doc: lircd manpage cleanup.

	doc: Fix some HTML and manpage syntax errors.

2015-02-12  Alec Leamas  <leamas.alec@gmail.com>

	irrecord: Add an --update option to merge new buttons
	Old code updated the pre/post data lengths even when using a template.
	This is OK when creating new file unrelated to the template, but
	does not allow merging of new buttons into an existing template file.

	The new option does not re-compute pre/post data, but instead verifies
	that the pre_data from the recorded buttons matches the recorded
	pre_data in global remote. Updating an existing file also affects how
	files are handled.

2015-02-12  Alec Leamas  <leamas.alec@gmail.com>

	irrecord-ui: Remove annoying "progname" in messages.

	irrecord-ui: Bugfix:  "Ask user for undefined remote name".

	irrecord: Enhance error message for unparsable files.

	irrecord, irrecord-ui: Use tmpfile as scratchpad, backup original file.
	Don't open output file until there is valid data to fill it with,
	and use a proper backup file. Use a temporary file for
	preliminary data.

2015-02-10  Alec Leamas  <leamas.alec@gmail.com>

	tools: Refactor drop_root setuid wrapper.

2015-02-10  Alec Leamas  <leamas.elac@nospam.net>

	irrecord: Handle multiple definitions, revise irrecord API (#78).
	To handle multiple definitions of the same key we need to
	store the recorded buttons as data before we write the
	file. Fixed, required a refresh of the irrecord lib
	API.

