2015-01-02  Alec Leamas  <leamas.alec@gmail.com>

	NEWS: update

	doc: Link driver documentation + misc manpages.
	Create  links to otherwise unlinked and hard to find html
	documents. Driver documents have a dynamic table of contents
	based on scanning for files with a _driver.html suffix.
	Existing driver documents is renamed to mmatch this pattern.

	doc: Use XSL to format pages instead of ad-hoc scripts (#14).

	doc: Fix html syntax errors.

	Contribute.md: Move new/removed drivers info to wiki.

	build: Distcheck bugfix, clean-up.

	contrib, doc: Remove outdated m4 lirc check macro.
	This is now handled by pkg-config config file lirc.pc.

2014-12-30  Alec Leamas  <leamas.alec@gmail.com>

	lirc.org: Fix configuration corner-cases & missing files.

2014-12-29  Inando  <inand0@users.sf.net>

	lirc.pc: Fix bad variable reference/ordering (#86)

	lirc.pc: Fix bad variable reference/ordering (#86)

2014-12-25  Alec Leamas  <leamas.alec@gmail.com>

	doc: Add missing file bugfix.

2014-12-19  Brian Moser  <moserb at users dot sf dot net>

	plugins: mplay bugfixes and overhaul.
	The mplay2 plugin for the Moneual MonCaso 312/320 pc cases does not work
	correctly. Some keys (for example REC, code 0x11) are, as far as I
	understand it, recognized as control characters and then ignored. Also
	the volume knob is not supported.

	There is a pretty old thread at ubuntuforums.org
	(http://ubuntuforums.org/showthread.php?t=1536934&p=12120799#post12120799)
	where the user Womiha provides a fix (which I tested and works), but it
	was never added to lirc. This patch is basically the same, rebased to
	0.9.2.

2014-12-19  Alec Leamas  <leamas.alec@gmail.com>

	doc: Add lirc.4 and lirc_ioctl.4 manpages.
	These pages describes kernel interfaces and should eventually
	be upstreamed, but will linger here for the time being. First
	we need to resolve the non-public header kernel bug 75751.

	lirc.org: Fix broken manpage links, missing images, merge release date.

	all: Fix mistaken puts() semantics in 85d4eb3.
	Dammit. puts() adds a trailing newline. Fix up accordingly.

2014-12-16  Alec Leamas  <leamas.alec@gmail.com>

	doc: Clean up irsend(1) manpage.

	lirc.h: Update bundled kernel header.

	configure.ac: Use pkg-config to locate ftdi.
	This picks up changed locations e. g., in fedora-22.

	all: Sanitize feature tests macros.

	all: Use puts() instead of printf() when applicable.
	Recent gcc compilers emits warnings when using printf() on
	constant data where puts()/fputs() is a better choice.

	lirc_options.conf: Add effective-user to template.

	tools: Make make_rel_symlink.py use python3.

	doc: Add Doxyfile to tarball.

	NEWS: merge release version.

